# JENKINS SETUP - GUIDE SIMPLE

## 1. PLUGINS (4 essentiels)

Jenkins → Manage Jenkins → Manage Plugins → Install:
- Docker Pipeline
- Pipeline
- Git plugin
- Credentials Binding

## 2. CREDENTIALS

Jenkins → Manage Jenkins → Manage Credentials → Add:
- Type: Username with password
- Username: admin
- Password: `<harbor_password>`
- ID: `harbor-credentials`

## 3. CRÉER LE JOB

Jenkins → New Item
- Name: `review-service-ci`
- Type: Multibranch Pipeline
- Repository URL: `https://gitlab.com/yourrepo/review-service.git`
- Script Path: `Jenkinsfile-ci`
- Save

## 4. DOCKER ACCESS

```bash
sudo usermod -aG docker jenkins
sudo systemctl restart jenkins
```

## 5. STRUCTURE REPO

```
review-service/
├── Jenkinsfile-ci
├── Dockerfile
├── src/
└── testapi/
    ├── data-test-api.sql
    └── test-api.sh
```

## 6. VARIABLES JENKINSFILE

```groovy
environment {
    HARBOR_REGISTRY = 'harbor.myvbox.com'
    HARBOR_PROJECT = 'ecommerce'
    DOCKER_IMAGE = 'review-service'
    DOCKER_TAG = 'v3.3'
}
```

## 7. PIPELINE STAGES

1. Initialisation → Echo infos
2. Test API → Tester endpoints (develop + main)
3. Build → docker build (develop + main)
4. Scan → Trivy scan (main seulement)
5. Push → Push to Harbor (main seulement)

## 8. WEBHOOK GITLAB (optionnel)

GitLab → Settings → Webhooks
- URL: `http://jenkins.myvbox.com/project/review-service-ci`
- Trigger: Push events

## 9. LANCER UN BUILD

Jenkins Dashboard → review-service-ci → Build Now

## 10. VOIR LES LOGS

Jenkins → review-service-ci → Build #X → Console Output

